  "prompt": "How can one tackle the increasing air pollution in Delhi?",
  "response": "To tackle air pollution in Delhi, a multi-pronged approach is necessary:\n\n1. Government Initiatives\n- Implement strict emission standards\n- Enforce vehicular pollution norms\n- Promote public transportation\n- Develop better urban planning\n- Introduce electric vehicles\n- Control construction dust\n\n2. Industrial Measures\n- Implement stricter industrial emission regulations\n- Promote cleaner technologies\n- Shift to renewable energy sources\n- Regulate industrial waste disposal\n\n3. Transportation Solutions\n- Improve public transportation infrastructure\n- Encourage carpooling\n- Promote electric and CNG vehicles\n- Implement odd-even vehicle rationing\n- Develop better cycling and walking infrastructure\n\n4. Agricultural Reforms\n- Ban crop burning\n- Provide alternative crop residue management techniques\n- Support farmers with technical and financial assistance\n\n5. Individual Actions\n- Use public transport\n- Reduce personal vehicle usage\n- Plant more trees\n- Use air purifiers\n- Wear masks during high pollution periods\n\n6. Long-term Strategies\n- Invest in green technologies\n- Develop comprehensive environmental policies\n- Create awareness about pollution's health impacts\n- Encourage sustainable urban development\n\n7. Technological Solutions\n- Use air quality monitoring systems\n- Develop innovative pollution reduction technologies\n\nCoordinated efforts from government, industries, and citizens are crucial for addressing Delhi's air pollution challenge.",
